name: Error, Talk not Found
description:
FREE EVENT

6:15: Networking
6:30: Talk: Error, Talk not Found - by Wilson Reid
7:00: QA
7:15: End of Meet up

Talk description: We are going to take a quick dive through exceptions, call stacks, HTTP codes, and possibly more! Then, we are going to take that information and apply it to actual examples. The goal is to become better developers by using error messages to find issues quickly and accurately. For most (seasoned developers in particular) this will likely be a refresher.

About the speaker: Wilson, graduated with honors from Red River College’s BIT program, works at SkipTheDishes as a Software Developer. He works with React, Java 8, and sometimes python 2.7. He also helps with onboarding (for React devs primarily). Fun fact, he plays drums.

Venue provided by Launch Coworking Space (https://launch1460.ca/) - Shared office space for freelancers, entrepreneurs, and small teams.

Sponsored by SkipTheDishes. skip will be proving pizzas for the event

name: Kotlin 101: Basic Concepts
description:
FREE EVENT

6:15: Networking
6:30: Talk: Kotlin 101: Basic Concepts - by Augusto A. B. Branquinho
7:00: QA
7:15: End of Meet up

About the talk: This talk will dive into the benefits and challenges of Kotlin programming language, talk a bit about its motivation, and go through its most important concepts as one of most powerful language out there.

About the speaker: Augusto is an experienced software engineer with more than 10 years of experience in the field. Currently working at SkipTheDishes as a senior software developer, Augusto has also a Ph.D. in Artificial Intelligence and Financial Market. He has great interests in Artificial Intelligence, Kotlin, Software Architecture, Functional Programming, and in IoT projects.

Twitter: @bbranquinho

Venue is provided by The Forth Cafe at 171 McDermot Avenue, Winnipeg http://www.forth.ca/
how_to_find_us: Gallery on the lower level - Use door on the side

6:15: Networking, Pizza and Cupcake
6:30: Talk: Jest - by Leonardo Vasconcelos
7:00: QA
7:15: End of Meet up

About the talk: This talk will explore some of the history and motivations that led to Jest testing framework creation. Going through examples and features that it uses, it will also dive into a quick look over performance options for React apps.

About the speaker: With Bachelor's Degree in Information Systems, Leo is a Senior React Developer at SkipTheDishes, Winnipeg. Recently moved from Brazil, Leo has been a developer for over 8 years working mostly with FE. In his spare time, Leo likes to play soccer with friends, play the drums whenever he has the chance, read the Bible, and talk about many topics with interesting people.

Twitter: @ ldvasc

Venue the Forth
Sponsorship SkiptheDishes http://www.skipthedishes.com and Cakeology https://www.cakeology.ca/

name: DevFest Winnipeg
description:
Detailed Location: Both days will be at the University of Winnipeg (515 Portage Ave, Winnipeg, MB R3B 2E9).

BUT, here is the exact location where the event will be held inside the university: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1uRrJivWG3sjcV4KkhpQxednVHhlwUv8p/view. The best entrance is on Ellice Avenue entrance on 490 Ellice Avenue, right on the DevFest text on the map.

--

REGISTER AT https://www.eventbrite.ca/e/gdg-winnipeg-devfest-2019-registration-55122804793

The biggest Google tech conference in Winnipeg carefully crafted for you by the GDG community! üéâ

Devfest Winnipeg is a community-run, one-day conference aimed to bring students, developers, tech-companies and awesome speakers together under one roof. Where they can learn about Google’s technologies along with other emerging technologies with topics such as Android, Flutter, Firebase, Google Cloud Platform, the Mobile Web, Google Assistant, Machine Learning and more.

The event will take place on February 23rd and 24th (Hackathon) in Winnipeg.

More information about the event will be announced soon, follow our social media to get the latest news about the event. @gdgwinnipeg

This event will be FREE and registration will be available soon!
